<exercise component="proteus" label="proteus-pos-neg"  xml:id="proteus-pos-neg" attachment="yes">
  <statement>
    <p>
      In part (a) of <xref ref="PA-1-4" text="type-global"/>, why do we get some positive and some negative values for <m>f'(a)</m>?  
    </p>
  </statement>
  <response />
</exercise>

<exercise component="proteus" label="proteus-represent"  xml:id="proteus-represent" attachment="yes">
  <statement>
    <p>
      <ol marker="(a)">
        <li>
          <p>
            In <m>f'(a)</m>, what does <m>a</m> represent? Is <m>a</m> an input? an output? a slope? a height?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What does <m>f'(a)</m> represent? Is <m>f'(a)</m> an input? an output? a slope? a height?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What do <m>f'(a)</m> and <m>a</m> have to do with each other?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What do <m>f'(a)</m> and <m>f(a)</m> have to do with each other?
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </statement>  
  <response />
</exercise>
